  "detailed_description": "<ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li> Roguelite catacombs that evolve and expand with each of your successes.<br></li><li> Hundreds of items, enemies and rooms, and dozens of epic boss fights.<br></li><li> Fully playable with keyboard+mouse or gamepad.<br></li><li> 5 difficulty levels range from &quot;Relatively Easy&quot; to &quot;Nigh Impossible.&quot;<br></li><li> Play as a &quot;head in a mech&quot; harvested from the neck of everyone's favorite Hydral.<br></li><li> Find secrets of The Megalith, a giant structure lodged in a star, as you lose many heads.<br></li><li> Figure out what happened to Rodney, an AI redshirt of uncertain motives.<br></li><li> Over-the-top mod support.  Detailed wiki: create enemies, items, weapons, and rooms.<br></li><li> Secrets!  Among them &quot;incredibilities&quot; that massively change the way the game plays.<br></li><li> Varied mech suits: dipole magnetism, time control, and more.<br></li><li> Upgrade during each &quot;run&quot; via EXP/Perks, shops, and items found while exploring.</li></ul>",
  "about_the_game": "<ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li> Roguelite catacombs that evolve and expand with each of your successes.<br></li><li> Hundreds of items, enemies and rooms, and dozens of epic boss fights.<br></li><li> Fully playable with keyboard+mouse or gamepad.<br></li><li> 5 difficulty levels range from &quot;Relatively Easy&quot; to &quot;Nigh Impossible.&quot;<br></li><li> Play as a &quot;head in a mech&quot; harvested from the neck of everyone's favorite Hydral.<br></li><li> Find secrets of The Megalith, a giant structure lodged in a star, as you lose many heads.<br></li><li> Figure out what happened to Rodney, an AI redshirt of uncertain motives.<br></li><li> Over-the-top mod support.  Detailed wiki: create enemies, items, weapons, and rooms.<br></li><li> Secrets!  Among them &quot;incredibilities&quot; that massively change the way the game plays.<br></li><li> Varied mech suits: dipole magnetism, time control, and more.<br></li><li> Upgrade during each &quot;run&quot; via EXP/Perks, shops, and items found while exploring.</li></ul>",
  "short_description": "A roguelite labyrinth lodged in the side of a star.  Dodge gorgeous waves of bullets, claim weapons and upgrades, defeat The Warden, and rescue... Rodney?",
  "supported_languages": "English<strong>*</strong><br><strong>*</strong>languages with full audio support",
  "reviews": "\u201cStarward Rogue is easily the best arcade roguelike since Binding of Isaac: Rebirth.\u201d<br>4.5/5 \u2013 <a href=\"https://steamcommunity.com/linkfilter/?url=http://www.hardcoregamer.com/2016/02/15/review-starward-rogue/190393/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"  >Hardcore Gamer</a></a><br><br>\u201cI've had a hoot of a time playing this game so far.\u201d<br><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QdGn8zdjpYE\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\"  >Scott Manley</a></a><br><br>\u201cThe Flame Tank I saw and instantaneously went &quot;Yep, that's my guy!&quot;\u201d<br><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ymFBYwpH7_I\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\"  >SplatterCat</a></a><br>",
